{
  "stem": "10768.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were really not Orthodox or in the midstream of, of Orthodox Jewish life.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was a predominantly Orthodox city.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we had organizations when-- the youth was always dragged in into Zionist organization.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Zionist movement was very, very pronounced and very strong.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "From Mizrahi and Orthodox, to-- from the extreme right to the extreme left, like Hashomer Hatzair, Hashomer Hadati, which were left.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the youth, even though they grew up in Orthodox home, was more modern.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They did not observe Saturday Shabbat as, let's say, our parents would, would expect it from us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Even-- I did not belong to organization because I left our town at the age of 13.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But while or before 13, I was never wearing at home, let's say, a dress with sleeves shorter above the, the elbow.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was always below.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This was the influence of my very ultra-Orthodox grandfather.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Saturday, if Father saw-- even Father, who was brought up in a more progressive home, if he saw me combing my hair or, or polishing my shoes, this was, let's say, taboo because it was Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So it was really a very, very strict Orthodox upbringing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lived, we lived in the Jewish neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Jewish neighborhood, we were-- our house-- next door to our house was a-- it was called a Sadigura shtiebel.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The names were usually after the type of Hasidim who, who believed in a certain rabbi.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Sadigura was a sect.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father was a Sadigura [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Sadigura rabbi was a more intelligent and more progressive-- I understand that he was born in Vienna during the Austrian, you know, time.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he had perhaps some education.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was more modern.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My grandfather was a Chortkiv rabbi.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
